snippet: A 2007 video of a boy chomping on the finger of his brother has been viewed 417.6 million times, making it the most successful noncommercial video in YouTube history.
abstract: Maidenhead Journal; video of a boy chomping on the finger of his brother, made in England in 2007, has been viewed 417.6 million times, making it the most successful noncommercial video in YouTube history and has made their family famous; the father is a YouTube 'partner,' meaning that the family shares in advertising revenue generated by the site; to date they have made enough money to pay for the boys' education.
lead_paragraph: A 2007 video of a boy chomping on the finger of his brother has been viewed 417.6 million times, making it the most successful noncommercial video in YouTube history.

headline.seo: ‘Charlie Bit My Finger’ Video Lifts Family to Fame
